      "name": "Worst-case operating-condition screening across 5 flow-speed combinations",
      "description": "CFD sweep executed across the declared CPB envelope (2.5, 4, 5, 6, 7 L/min at 2500-4000 rpm). Ranking of hemolysis severity is reported, and the 7 L/min / 4000 rpm condition is identified as worst-case. Predicted MIH values across the sweep are consistent with the power-law trend observed in single-point validation and with qualitative expectations from the FDA CFD round-robin. No per-condition experimental comparator is enumerated here because the Herbertson dataset establishes baseline model fidelity for this geometry.",
